    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss> Files: <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    118 Series</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Executive Secretary of the National Security
                        Council</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">National Security
                            Council</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-19">December 19,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: United States Objectives and Courses of Action in
                    Korea</p>
                <p>
                    <list type="references">
                        <item>References: A. <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1 and Annex to
                                <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1<note n="1"
                                xml:id="d855fn1">See <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1,
                                dated December 7, <ref target="#pg_1259">p. 1259</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item>B. Memo for <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> from Executive
                            Secretary, same subject, dated December 18, 1951<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d855fn2">Not printed.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The Senior <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff, having reviewed the
                    statement of policy contained in <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1 in
                    the light of the views of the Joint Chiefs of Staff and after further study by
                    the interested departments and agencies, recommends the following revisions in
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1 to the National Security Council
                    for consideration at its meeting on December 19:<note n="3" xml:id="d855fn3">The
                        paragraphs of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1 under reference are:
                            1<hi rend="italic">a</hi>(4), 2<hi rend="italic">a</hi>(4, 5, and 6),
                        and 2<hi rend="italic">b</hi> (3).</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Page 2, subparagraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">4</hi>)<hi
                        rend="italic">:</hi> Revise to read as follows:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>(4) Permit the building of sufficient <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>
                        military power to deter or repel a renewed aggression by North Korean forces
                        alone.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Page 3, subparagraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">4</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">5th line of the subparagraph:</hi> Place a period after
                    “security of the <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>” and delete the remainder
                    of the subparagraph.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Page 4, subparagraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">5</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">next to last line of the subparagraph:</hi> Delete “the heads
                    of”.</p>
                <pb facs="1391" n="1375" xml:id="pg_1375"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Page 4, subparagraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">6</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">4th line of the subparagraph:</hi> Place a period after
                    “terms” and delete the remainder of the subparagraph.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Page 5, subparagraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">3</hi>)<hi
                        rend="italic">:</hi> In the first line substitute “any” for “all”; in the
                    second line after “against” insert “air”.</p>
                <p>The Senior <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff also concurred in the view
                    of the Joint Chiefs of Staff as expressed in paragraph 2 <hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi> of Reference B that <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1 is
                    intended to amend only subparagraphs 6 <hi rend="italic">e</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">f</hi> and paragraph 9 of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    48/5. It is suggested that a statement along the lines recommended by the Joint
                    Chiefs of Staff be incorporated in the “Note by the Executive Secretary” when a
                    revised version of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 118/1 as amended is
                    reproduced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay,
                        Jr</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
